GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 2
SENATE BILL 214
Finance Committee Substitute Adopted 3/18/25
Short Title: Four Oaks/Creedmoor Deannexations. (Local)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
March 3, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REMOVING CERTAIN DESCRIBED PROPERTY FROM THE CORPORATE
3 LIMITS OF THE TOWN OF FOUR OAKS AND THE CITY OF CREEDMOOR.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1.(a) The following described property is removed from the corporate
6 limits of the Town of Four Oaks:
7 TRACT I:
8 Being all of Area 1, containing 11.609 acres, more or less, as shown on that map entitled
9 "Estate Division by Will Plat for Bill Ray Price Estate" recorded in Map Book 95, Page 204 of
10 the Johnston County Registry.
11 TRACT II:
12 Being all of that certain tract or parcel of land described as "Remaining Combined Area,"
13 containing 14.432 acres, more or less, as shown on that map entitled "Minor Subdivision Plat for
14 Pamela Rae Price" recorded in Map Book 96, Page 278 of the Johnston County Registry.
15 SECTION 1.(b) This section has no effect upon the validity of any liens of the Town
16 of Four Oaks for ad valorem taxes or special assessments outstanding before the effective date
17 of this section. Such liens may be collected or foreclosed upon after the effective date of this
18 section as though the property were still within the corporate limits of the Town of Four Oaks.
19 SECTION 1.(c) This section becomes effective June 30, 2025. Property in the
20 territory described in Section 1(a) of this act as of January 1, 2025, is no longer subject to
21 municipal taxes for taxes imposed for taxable years beginning on or after July 1, 2025.
22 SECTION 2.(a) The following described property, identified by Granville County
23 Tax Property Identification Number, is removed from the corporate limits of the City of
24 Creedmoor: 180603417847.
25 SECTION 2.(b) This section has no effect upon the validity of any liens of the City
26 of Creedmoor for ad valorem taxes or special assessments outstanding before the effective date
27 of this section. Such liens may be collected or foreclosed upon after the effective date of this
28 section as though the property were still within the corporate limits of the City of Creedmoor.
29 SECTION 2.(c) This section becomes effective June 30, 2025. Property in the
30 territory described in Section 2(a) of this act as of January 1, 2025, is no longer subject to
31 municipal taxes for taxes imposed for taxable years beginning on or after July 1, 2025.
32 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
33 law.
*S214-v-2*

